name: Treasury
description:
The Treasury unlocks access to the Lockbox, increases the mining speed and protected cargo of Survey ships, and increases the cargo capacity of all ships.

Upgrading the Treasury to level 40 adds bonus Prime Particles to the daily Optical Diodes claim in the gift section of the store until all Prime Territory research is completed.

description: The Shipyard is instrumental in ship construction. Upgrade this building to get access to more ships and increase the speed of ship construction.

name: Ship Hangar
description: The Ship Hangar is where extra ships are stored when they are not currently used in the active fleet. Upgrade the Hangar to increase the amount of Ships that can be owned.

description: The Armada Control Center allows you to initiate Armada attacks on hostile targets. Upgrade the Center to increase the number of allied ships that can join your Armada attacks.

description: Here is where your Officers stay when they are not assigned. Promote and Level your Officers via the Officer Screen.

name: R&D Department
description: The Research Lab is vital for the discovery of new technologies. Here, new Ships, buildings or supporting technologies are unlocked.

name: Astronautics Studio
description: New ship hulls are researched and unlocked here before becoming available in the Shipyard.

name: Armory
description:
The Armory allows access to ship refits that unlock new active abilities, as well as increasing the Hull Health, Shield Health, and Mitigation stats of all ships. 

Upgrading the Armory to certain levels will also grant enough refit shards to fully unlock the refits for specific ships. 

Level 26: Mayflower, D3, Legionary
Level 28: Saladin, Bortas, Centurion
Level 42: Kelvin, K'T'inga, Valdore
Level 53: Northcutt, Vor'cha, Corvus

name: Holodeck
description:
Build in order to gain access to the <color=#ffc926>Holodeck</color> to purchase missions from previous arcs. The <color=#ffc926>Holodeck</color> increases base Piercing stats for all ships, base Materials Cost Efficiency for ship upgrades and base FKR reputation from hostiles and armadas. 

At Operations level 32 with the <color=#ffc926>Holodeck</color> unlocked you get a daily gift of Holo-Field Amplifiers.

Every 5 levels of the <color=#ffc926>Holodeck</color>, unlock new missions, and receive shards for Enterprise E Data, Enterprise E Troi and Enterprise E Picard from the Holodeck section of the Recruit Store.

name: Subspace Relay
description: Constructed with the aid of ancient Progenitor architectural drawings. Activates the station as a node on the Progenitor Subspace Network, allowing allied stations to instantly share computational processing power across vast distances.

name: Command Center
description: Enter into <color=#ffc926>Command Center</color> to assign your <color=#ffc926>Fleet Commanders</color> in order to optimize your fleet's capabilities.

name: Mess Hall
description: The Mess Hall is the heart and soul of any station or ship. Crew members come together between shifts or for meal times here. At peak hours, this is the busiest part of any facility. With a bustling Mess Hall, even the deepest reaches of distant space can feel just like home.

name: Artifact Gallery
description: The Artifact Gallery houses a collection of valuable artifacts that have been acquired from across the quadrant and beyond. Visitors to the station are welcome to see these rare and fascinating objects on display.

name: Court of Q
description: The benevolent Q has graced your station with his presence and left an impressionable mark upon the Court. By adding opulence and grandeur to the Court of Q, the building will grant you greater rewards and access to more of Q's Trials.

name: The Facade
description:
A mysterious building and a front for an even more mysterious organization. The Facade increases base Damage of ships in Wave Defense, base Hull Health for all ships and base Officer Stats. 

If you have unlocked Armada Quick Start in the Section 31 Faction, the daily gift of Armada Countdown Speed Ups is increased.

name: The War Room
description: The War Room serves as your connection to the Order of Kotal - a secret order of warriors doing battle to prove their honor and earn the ultimate rewards. Upgrade the War Room to increase Warchest rewards, Isolytic Damage, Officer Stats, and Shield Health.

name: District 56
description:
In the world of an Independent contractor, no Station is complete without a bustling hub of trade, entertainment... and the occasional black market deal. When it comes to rest, relaxation and risky ventures, <color=#ffc926>District 56</color> has everything that a dedicated Independent could ever need.

Every 5 levels upgraded in <color=#ffc926>District 56</color> resets the cooldown and increases the rewards given in the <color=#ffc926>District 56</color> free claim in the <color=#FFC926>Mirror Refinery</color>.

name: The Nova Squadron
description: The Nova Squadron building is where the most promising cadets train to become the next generation of elite Starfleet officers. The skill within increases SHP, Cost Efficiency for Building Materials, and Weapon Damage.
